= {{Plainlist|\n* [[Warner Bros. Pictures]] (Worldwide)\n* Toho (Japan)\n}}\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|11|20|United States}}\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         =\n| gross          =\n}}\n\n'''''Godzilla vs. Kong''''' is an upcoming American [[monster film]] directed by [[Adam Wingard]]. A sequel to ''[[Godzilla: King of the Monsters (2019 film)|Godzilla: King of the Monsters]]'' (2019) and ''[[Kong: Skull Island]]'' (2017), it is the fourth film in [[Legendary Entertainment|Legendary]]'s [[MonsterVerse]]. The film is also the 36th film in the [[Godzilla (franchise)|''Godzilla'' franchise]], the 12th film in the [[King Kong (franchise)|''King Kong'' franchise]], and the fourth ''Godzilla'' film to be completely produced by a Hollywood studio.{{efn|The American releases of ''[[Godzilla (1954 film)|Godzilla]]'' (''[[Godzilla, King of the Monsters!]]''), ''[[King Kong vs. Godzilla#English version|King Kong vs. Godzilla]]'', and ''[[The Return of Godzilla]]'' (''[[Godzilla 1985]]'') featured additional footage with American actors filmed by small Hollywood production companies that merged the American footage with the original Japanese footage in order to appeal to American audiences.{{sfn|Kalat|2010|p=25}} ''[[Invasion of Astro-Monster]]'' was the first ''Godzilla'' film to be co-produced between a Japanese studio (Toho) and an American studio ([[UPA (animation studio)|UPA]]). The first ''Godzilla'' film to be completely produced by a Hollywood studio was ''[[Godzilla (1998 film)|Godzilla]]'' (1998).}} The film stars [[Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd]], [[Millie Bobby Brown]], [[Rebecca Hall]], [[Brian Tyree Henry]], [[Shun Oguri]], [[Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez]], [[Jessica Henwick]], [[Julian Dennison]], [[Kyle Chandler]], [[Zhang Ziyi]], and [[Demi\u00e1n Bichir]].\n\nThe project was announced in October 2015 when Legendary announced plans for a shared cinematic universe between [[Godzilla]] and [[King Kong]]. The film's writers room was assembled in March 2017, and Wingard was announced as the director in May 2017. [[Principal photography]] began in November 2018 in [[Hawaii]], [[Australia]], and [[Hong Kong]] and [[Wrap (filmmaking)|wrapped]] in April 2019. ''Godzilla vs. Kong'' is scheduled to be released on November 20, 2020, in 2D, [[3D film|3D]], and [[IMAX]].\n\n==Premise==\n{{quote|In a time when monsters walk the Earth, humanity's fight for its future sets Godzilla and Kong on a collision course that will see the two most powerful forces of nature on the planet collide in a spectacular battle for the ages. As Monarch embarks on a perilous mission into uncharted terrain and unearths clues to the Titans' origins, a human conspiracy threatens to wipe the creatures, both good and bad, from the face of the earth forever.|source=Legendary and Warner Bros.<ref name=\"Press Release\"/>}}\n\n== Cast ==\n*[[Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd]]:<br>A [[geologist]] who works closely with Kong. Skarsg\u00e5rd described his character as a [[reluctant hero]] who is \"not an alpha, bad-ass\" and \"thrown into this very dangerous situation and is definitely not equipped for it\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://etcanada.com/news/383733/alexander-skarsgard-spills-details-about-his-role-in-godzilla-vs-king-kong/|title=Alexander Skarsgard Spills Details About His Role In \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019|author=Brent Furdyk|work=Entertainment Tonight Canada|date=November 5, 2018|accessdate=October 14, 2019|url-status=live|archivedate=October 14, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191015021004/https://etcanada.com/news/383733/alexander-skarsgard-spills-details-about-his-role-in-godzilla-vs-king-kong/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://collider.com/alexander-skarsgard-the-kill-team-the-stand-godzilla-vs-kong-interview/|title=Alexander Skarsgard on 'The Kill Team', 'The Stand', and His Unlikely Hero in 'Godzilla vs. Kong'|last=Radish|first=Christina|date=2019-10-30|website=Collider|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/18/movies/alexander-skarsgard-the-kill-team.html|title=There Are Worse Roles Than the Seducer. Ask Alexander Skarsgard.|last=Shattuck|first=Kathryn|date=2019-10-18|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-11-09|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n*[[Millie Bobby Brown]] as Madison Russell\n*[[Rebecca Hall]]\n*[[Brian Tyree Henry]]\n*[[Shun Oguri]]\n*[[Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez]]:<br>Gonz\u00e1lez described her role as a \"very smart woman behind a company\". She also described the film as \"slightly comedic\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://collider.com/eiza-gonzalez-bloodshot-paradise-hills-interview/|title=Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez on 'Paradise Hills' and Playing the First Female Mexican Superhero in 'Bloodshot'|last=Radish|first=Christina|date=2019-10-31|website=Collider|language=en-US|url-status=live|access-date=2019-11-09}}</ref>\n*[[Jessica Henwick]]\n*[[Julian Dennison]]\n*[[Kyle Chandler]] as Dr. Mark Russell:<br>Madison's father and an expert [[Anthrozoology|anthrozoologist]].\n*[[Demi\u00e1n Bichir]]\n\nAdditionally, [[Zhang Ziyi]] reprises her role from ''Godzilla: King of the Monsters'', with Van Marten cast as her assistant. [[Lance Reddick]] has been cast in an undisclosed role.\n\n== Production ==\n'''Production credits'''<ref name=\"Press Release\"/>\n{{Div col}}\n* [[Adam Wingard]] \u2013 director\n* Kenji Okuhira \u2013 executive producer\n* [[Yoshimitsu Banno]] \u2013 executive producer (posthumous)\n* [[Jon Jashni]] \u2013 executive producer\n* [[Thomas Tull]] \u2013 executive producer\n* Jay Ashenfelter \u2013 co-producer\n* Jen Conroy \u2013 co-producer\n* Tamara Kent \u2013 co-producer\n* Owen Patterson \u2013 production designer\n* Tom Hammock \u2013 production designer\n* Ann Foley \u2013 costume designer\n* John \u201cDJ\u201d DesJardin \u2013 VFX supervisor\n{{Div col end}}\n\n===Development===\nIn September 2015, Legendary moved ''Kong: Skull Island'' from Universal to Warner Bros., which sparked media speculation that [[Godzilla]] and [[King Kong]] would appear in a film together.<ref name=\"KingKongOnMove\">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2015/09/king-kong-godzilla-legendary-monster-movie-warner-bros-1201521004/ |title=King Kong On Move To Warner Bros, Presaging Godzilla Monster Matchup |last=Fleming Jr. |first=Mike |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=September 10, 2015 |accessdate=September 10, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150911232832/http://deadline.com/2015/09/king-kong-godzilla-legendary-monster-movie-warner-bros-1201521004/#|archive-date=September 11, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |work=The Hollywood Reporter |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hollywood-gorilla-warfare-s-universal-823715 |title=Hollywood Gorilla Warfare: It\u2019s Universal vs. Legendary Over \u2018Kong: Skull Island\u2019 (and Who Says \"Thank You\") |first=Kim |last=Masters |date=September 16, 2015 |accessdate=September 17, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150917235805/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hollywood-gorilla-warfare-s-universal-823715# |archive-date=September 17, 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref> In October 2015, Legendary confirmed that they would unite Godzilla and King Kong in ''Godzilla vs. Kong'', at the time targeted for a May 29, 2020, release. Legendary plans to create a shared cinematic franchise \"centered around Monarch\" that \"brings together Godzilla and Legendary\u2019s King Kong in an ecosystem of other [[kaiju|giant super-species]], both classic and new.\"<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.legendary.com/legendary-and-warner-bros-pictures-announce-cinematic-franchise-uniting-godzilla-king-kong-and-other-iconic-giant-monsters/ |title=Legendary and Warner Bros. Pictures Announce Cinematic Franchise Uniting Godzilla, King Kong and Other Iconic Giant Monsters |publisher=Legendary Pictures |date=October 14, 2015 |accessdate=October 14, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151105182819/http://www.legendary.com/legendary-and-warner-bros-pictures-announce-cinematic-franchise-uniting-godzilla-king-kong-and-other-iconic-giant-monsters/#|archive-date=November 5, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> Producer Alex Garcia confirmed that the film will not be a [[remake]] of ''[[King Kong vs. Godzilla]]'', stating, \"the idea is not to remake that movie.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tohokingdom.com/interviews/kong_alex_garcia_02-2017.html |title=Interview: Alex Garcia \u2013 Roundtable (2015) |last=Mirjahangir |first=Chris |website=Toho Kingdom |date=December 2, 2015 |accessdate=July 14, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170619160700/http://www.tohokingdom.com/interviews/kong_alex_garcia_02-2017.html#|archive-date=June 19, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In May 2017, [[Adam Wingard]] was announced as the director for ''Godzilla vs. Kong''.<ref name=\"Adam\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/godzilla-kong-finds-director-adam-wingard-1008773 |title='Godzilla vs. Kong' Finds Its Director With Adam Wingard (Exclusive) |last=Kit |first=Borys |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=May 30, 2017 |accessdate=May 30, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170531025423/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/godzilla-kong-finds-director-adam-wingard-1008773#|archive-date=May 31, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2017, Wingard spoke about the outline created by the writers room, stating, \"We're going in very great detail through all the characters, the arcs they have, how they relate to one another, and most importantly how they relate to the monsters, and how the monsters relate to them or reflect them.\" He also stated that he and his team are going \"beat by beat\" on the outline, stating, \"So once again, it's a discussion, and about feeling out how to make it as strong as possible, so that when Terry [Rossio] goes to write the screenplay, he has a definitive breakdown of what to include.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/07/20/adam-wingard-talks-godzilla-vs.-kong-and-directorial-freedom |title=Adam Wingard Talks Godzilla vs. Kong And Directorial Freedom |last=Gingold |first=Michael |work=Birth.Movies.Death |date=July 20, 2017 |accessdate=July 20, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723234247/http://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/07/20/adam-wingard-talks-godzilla-vs.-kong-and-directorial-freedom#|archive-date=July 23, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In August 2017, Wingard spoke about his approach for the monsters, stating:\n\n{{Quote|\"I really want you to take those characters seriously. I want you to be emotionally invested, not just in the human characters, but actually in the monsters. It\u2019s a massive monster brawl movie. There\u2019s lots of monsters going crazy on each other, but at the end of the day I want there to be an emotional drive to it. I want you to be emotionally invested in them. I think that\u2019s what\u2019s going to make it really cool.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://screencrush.com/adam-wingard-godzilla-vs-kong-emotional/ |title=Adam Wingard Wants 'Godzilla vs. Kong' to Make You Cry |last=Whitney |first=E. Oliver |work=Screen Crush |date=August 18, 2017 |accessdate=August 19, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170819034438/http://screencrush.com/adam-wingard-godzilla-vs-kong-emotional/#|archive-date=2017-08-19|url-status=live}}</ref>}} Wingard expressed his desire for the film to have a definite winner, stating:\n\n{{Quote|\u201cI do want there to be a winner. The original film was very fun, but you feel a little let down that the movie doesn\u2019t take a definitive stance. People are still debating now who won in that original movie, you know. So, I do want people to walk away from this film feeling like, Okay, there is a winner.\u201d<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiewire.com/2017/08/godzilla-vs-kong-adam-wingard-winner-1201868084/ |title=\u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019: Adam Wingard Says the Epic Battle Will Have a Definitive Winner |last=Nordine |first=Michael |work=IndieWire |date=August 20, 2017 |accessdate=January 8, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180109121908/http://www.indiewire.com/2017/08/godzilla-vs-kong-adam-wingard-winner-1201868084/#|archive-date=2018-01-09|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\nWingard also confirmed that the film will tie in with ''[[Godzilla: King of the Monsters (2019 film)|Godzilla: King of the Monsters]]'', be set in modern times, and feature a \"more rugged, a bit more aged Kong.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://screenrant.com/godzilla-vs-kong-setting-character-details/?view=lista |title=Godzilla vs. Kong Set in Modern Day, Ties to Godzilla 2 |last=Mithaiwala |first=Mansoor |work=Screen Rant |date=August 22, 2017 |accessdate=August 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171224101315/https://screenrant.com/godzilla-vs-kong-setting-character-details/?view=lista#|archive-date=December 24, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Writing===\nIn March 2017, Legendary assembled a writers room to develop the story for ''Godzilla vs. Kong'', with [[Terry Rossio]] (who co-wrote an early unproduced script for [[Godzilla (1998 film)|TriStar's ''Godzilla'']])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2015/05/10/godzilla-unmade-the-history-of-jan-de-bonts-unproduced-tristar-film-part-1/ |title=Godzilla Unmade: The History of Jan De Bont\u2019s Unproduced TriStar Film \u2013 Part 1 of 4 |last=Aiken |first=Keith |website=Scifi Japan |date=May 10, 2015 |accessdate=May 23, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915071019/http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2015/05/10/godzilla-unmade-the-history-of-jan-de-bonts-unproduced-tristar-film-part-1/#|archive-date=September 15, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> leading a team consisting of Patrick McKay, J. D. Payne, Lindsey Beer, Cat Vasko, [[T.S. Nowlin]], Jack Paglen, and [[J. Michael Straczynski]].<ref name=\"writers room\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/kong-skull-island-sequel-plans-godzilla-kong-sets-writers-room-984992 |title='Godzilla vs. Kong' Film Sets Writers Room (Exclusive) |last=Kit |first=Borys |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=March 10, 2017 |accessdate=March 10, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170310230537/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/kong-skull-island-sequel-plans-godzilla-kong-sets-writers-room-984992#|archive-date=March 10, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On his experience with the writers room, Rossio stated:\n\n{{Quote|\"''Godzilla vs. Kong'' was my first experience running a writer's room, and it was fantastic. It was a blast reading samples, meeting different writers, and crafting a story in a group setting. It felt similar to animation, where the film is happening up on the walls, and the end result is better than any one person could accomplish on their own.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/pirates-caribbean-screenwriter-how-a-budget-crisis-changed-villains-1001860 |title=Original 'Pirates of the Caribbean' Screenwriter on How a Budget Crisis Changed the Villains |last=Schoellkopf |first=Christina |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=May 26, 2017 |accessdate=May 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170527023430/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/pirates-caribbean-screenwriter-how-a-budget-crisis-changed-villains-1001860#|archive-date=May 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\n[[Michael Dougherty]] and Zach Shields, the director and co-writers of ''Godzilla: King of the Monsters'', provided rewrites to ensure that certain themes from ''King of the Monsters'' were carried over and that some characters were properly developed.<ref>{{cite web |last=Tyler |first=Jacob |url=https://thegww.com/godzilla-vs-kong-got-rewrites-from-mike-dougherty-zach-shields-godzilla-king-of-the-monsters/ |title=''Godzilla vs. Kong'' Got Rewrites From Mike Dougherty & Zach Shields |date=March 5, 2019 |work=Omega Underground |accessdate=March 13, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=March 13, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190314023922/https://thegww.com/godzilla-vs-kong-got-rewrites-from-mike-dougherty-zach-shields-godzilla-king-of-the-monsters/}}</ref> Dougherty revealed how he wrote for the title characters, and how the film would address their differing interactions with people. For Kong, Dougherty stated the film would feature \"those very unique, and even warm, bonding moments\" between Kong and humans since they've been a staple of the character since the [[King Kong (1933 film)|1933 film]]. For Godzilla, his connection to humans would be \"more implied\" as his softer side is rarely shown.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/godzilla-king-kong-different-humanity-connections-explained/ |title=Godzilla 2 Director Explains Godzilla & Kong's Different Connections to Humanity |first=Daniel |last=Alvarez |work=Screen Rant |date=May 5, 2019 |accessdate=May 7, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=May 7, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190507185131/https://screenrant.com/godzilla-king-kong-different-humanity-connections-explained/}}</ref>\n\n=== Pre-production ===\nIn June 2017, it was announced that [[Ziyi Zhang]] had joined Legendary's MonsterVerse, having a reportedly \"pivotal\" role in both ''Godzilla: King of the Monsters'' and ''Godzilla vs. Kong''.<ref name=\"ZiyiCast\">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2017/06/zhang-ziyi-godzilla-movie-franchise-casting-1202110018/ |title=Zhang Ziyi Comes Aboard 'Godzilla' And Beyond |last=Hipes |first=Patrick |website=Deadline.com |date=June 8, 2017 |accessdate=June 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611233620/http://deadline.com/2017/06/zhang-ziyi-godzilla-movie-franchise-casting-1202110018/#|archive-date=June 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2018, [[Julian Dennison]] was cast alongside Van Marten, while [[Millie Bobby Brown]] and [[Kyle Chandler]] would reprise their roles from ''Godzilla: King of the Monsters''.<ref>{{cite web |last=Perez |first=Lexy |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/deadpool-2-star-julian-dennison-joins-godzilla-kong-1116661 |title=''Deadpool 2'' Star Julian Dennison Joins ''Godzilla vs. Kong'' |date=June 2, 2018 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=June 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180603033211/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/deadpool-2-star-julian-dennison-joins-godzilla-kong-1116661#|archive-date=June 3, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Legendary also sent an offer to [[Frances McDormand]] for a role.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thathashtagshow.com/2018/06/exclusive-deadpool-2-julian-dennison-joins-godzilla-vs-kong/ |title=Exclusive: \u2018Deadpool 2\u2019s\u2019 Julian Dennison Joins \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 |last=Murphy |first=Charles |work=That Hashtag Show |date=June 1, 2018 |accessdate=June 1, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143532/http://thathashtagshow.com/2018/06/exclusive-deadpool-2-julian-dennison-joins-godzilla-vs-kong/|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> In July 2018, it was revealed that [[Danai Gurira]] was in early talks to join the film.<ref name=\"Danai Guiridia\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/danai-gurira-godzilla-vs-kong-star-trek-the-walking-dead-black-panther-1202425900/ |title=Danai Gurira In Early \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 Talks As \u2018Star Trek\u2019 Also Looms For \u2018Walking Dead\u2019 & \u2018Black Panther\u2019 Star |first=Mike |last=Fleming Jr. |work=Deadline |date=July 12, 2018 |accessdate=July 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180713054816/https://deadline.com/2018/07/danai-gurira-godzilla-vs-kong-star-trek-the-walking-dead-black-panther-1202425900/#|archive-date=July 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In October 2018, [[Brian Tyree Henry]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/brian-tyree-henry-godzilla-vs-kong-millie-bobby-brown-1202976259/ |title=Brian Tyree Henry to Co-Star With Millie Bobby Brown in \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 (Exclusive) |first=Justin |last=Kroll |work=Variety |date=October 10, 2018 |accessdate=October 10, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011014559/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/brian-tyree-henry-godzilla-vs-kong-millie-bobby-brown-1202976259/#|archive-date=October 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Demi\u00e1n Bichir]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Kit |first=Borys |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/demi-n-bichir-joining-millie-bobby-brown-godzilla-kong-1153121 |title=Demi\u00e1n Bichir Joining Millie Bobby Brown in ''Godzilla vs. Kong'' |date=October 17, 2018 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher=[[Valence Media]] |accessdate=October 17, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181017213127/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/demi-n-bichir-joining-millie-bobby-brown-godzilla-kong-1153121|archive-date=October 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd]],<ref name=\"Skarsg\u00e5rdCast\">{{cite news |last1=Jr |first1=Mike Fleming |title=Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd To Star In \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/alexander-skarsgard-to-star-in-godzilla-vs-kong-1202489612/ |accessdate=October 25, 2018 |work=Deadline |date=October 25, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181026064527/https://deadline.com/2018/10/alexander-skarsgard-to-star-in-godzilla-vs-kong-1202489612/# |archive-date=October 26, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/eiza-gonzalez-godzilla-vs-king-kong-alexander-skarsgard-1202492406/ |title=Eiza Gonzalez Joins \u2018Godzilla Vs. King Kong |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |first=Mike |last=Fleming Jr |date=October 30, 2018 |accessdate=October 30, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031052347/https://deadline.com/2018/10/eiza-gonzalez-godzilla-vs-king-kong-alexander-skarsgard-1202492406/#|archive-date=October 31, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Rebecca Hall]] were added to the cast.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/rebecca-hall-godzilla-vs-kong-1203014950/ |title=Rebecca Hall to Star Opposite Millie Bobby Brown in \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 (EXCLUSIVE) |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |first=Justin |last=Kroll |date=October 30, 2018 |accessdate=October 30, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031005404/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/rebecca-hall-godzilla-vs-kong-1203014950/#|archive-date=October 31, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2018, [[Jessica Henwick]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/jessica-henwick-godzilla-vs-kong-game-of-thrones-1203024081/ |title=\u2018Game of Thrones\u2019 Actress Jessica Henwick Joins \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 (Exclusive) |first=Justin |last=Kroll |work=Variety |date=November 8, 2018 |accessdate=November 8, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181109070757/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/jessica-henwick-godzilla-vs-kong-game-of-thrones-1203024081/|archive-date=November 9, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Shun Oguri]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/shun-oguri-godzilla-vs-kong-japanese-star-crows-zero-alexander-skarsgard-1202499759/ |title=Japanese Star Shun Oguri Makes Hollywood Debut In \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 |first=Mike |last=Fleming Jr |work=Deadline |date=November 11, 2018 |accessdate=November 11, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181111213802/https://deadline.com/2018/11/shun-oguri-godzilla-vs-kong-japanese-star-crows-zero-alexander-skarsgard-1202499759/#|archive-date=November 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Lance Reddick]] were cast, with Oguri making his Hollywood debut.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/bosch-lance-reddick-godzilla-vs-kong-1202502022/ |title='Bosch' Actor Lance Reddick Cast in 'Godzilla vs Kong' |website=Deadline |first=Amanda |last=N'Duka |date=November 14, 2018 |accessdate=November 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181115030528/https://deadline.com/2018/11/bosch-lance-reddick-godzilla-vs-kong-1202502022/|archive-date=November 15, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\n[[Principal photography]] began on November 12, 2018 in [[Hawaii]] and [[Australia]] and was expected to end in February 2019 under the working title ''Apex''.<ref name=\"Press Release\">{{cite web |url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20181112005664/en/Warner-Bros.-Pictures%E2%80%99-Legendary-Entertainment%E2%80%99s-Monsterverse-Shifts |title=Warner Bros. Pictures\u2019 and Legendary Entertainment\u2019s Monsterverse Shifts into Overdrive as Cameras Roll on the Next Big-Screen Adventure \"Godzilla Vs. Kong\" |work=Business Wire |date= |accessdate=November 12, 2018 |archivedate=January 19, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190120054526/https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20181112005664/en/Warner-Bros.-Pictures%E2%80%99-Legendary-Entertainment%E2%80%99s-Monsterverse-Shifts|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Prasad |first=R.A |url=https://pursuenews.com/godzilla-vs-kong-working-title-revealed/ |title=Warner Bros. And Legendary Pictures' ''Godzilla Vs. Kong'' Working Title Revealed |date=May 3, 2018 |publisher=PureNews |accessdate=May 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180504092023/https://pursuenews.com/godzilla-vs-kong-working-title-revealed/#|archive-date=May 4, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Production was initially slated to begin on October 1, 2018.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Marc |first1=Christopher |title='Godzilla vs Kong' Heading Back To Australia and Hawaii - GWW |url=https://thegww.com/godzilla-vs-kong-heading-back-to-australia-and-hawaii/ |accessdate=July 18, 2018 |work=GWW |date=July 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011053715/https://thegww.com/godzilla-vs-kong-heading-back-to-australia-and-hawaii/# |archive-date=October 11, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> For the Hawaii shoot, the crew filmed on the [[USS Missouri (BB-63)|USS ''Missouri'']], at [[Manoa Falls]], and in [[Downtown Honolulu]]. The crew established a camp in the [[Hawaii Route 72|Kalanianaole Highway]], which had been closed until November 21. Local crews and extras were used for the film.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.staradvertiser.com/2018/11/16/hawaii-news/godzilla-vs-kong-filming-in-full-swing-with-upcoming-closures-on-oahu/ |title=\u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 filming in full swing with upcoming closures on Oahu |first=Nina |last=Wu |work=Star Advertiser |date=November 17, 2018 |accessdate=November 17, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181117114833/http://www.staradvertiser.com/2018/11/16/hawaii-news/godzilla-vs-kong-filming-in-full-swing-with-upcoming-closures-on-oahu/|archive-date=November 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2019, filming resumed in [[Gold Coast, Queensland]] at [[Village Roadshow Studios]] for an additional 26 weeks.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/national/queensland/godzilla-vs-kong-begins-filming-on-the-gold-coast-20190118-p50s6d.html |title=Godzilla vs. Kong begins filming on the Gold Coast |first=Felicity |last=Caldwell |work=Brisbane Times |date=January 18, 2019 |accessdate=January 19, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190119224354/https://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/national/queensland/godzilla-vs-kong-begins-filming-on-the-gold-coast-20190118-p50s6d.html |archivedate=January 19, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Godzilla sighting down under! |url=https://moviehole.net/godzilla-sighting-down-under/ |website=Moviehole |publisher=Editorial Staff |accessdate=January 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190124034500/https://moviehole.net/godzilla-sighting-down-under/ |archive-date=January 24, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nFilming locations in Australia included [[Miami State High School]] and parts of [[Brisbane]] such as the [[Newstead, Queensland|Newstead suburb]], the [[Chinatown, Brisbane|Chinatown Mall in Fortitude Valley]], and the [[Wickham Terrace Car Park]]. In April 2019, Wingard confirmed via [[Instagram]] that filming in Australia had wrapped.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2470013/Godzilla-Vs-Kong-Has-Wrapped-In-Australia-According-To-The-Director |title=Godzilla Vs. Kong Has Wrapped In Australia |first=Dirk |last=Libbey |work=Cinema Blend |date=April 9, 2019 |accessdate=April 9, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=April 9, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410020411/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2470013/Godzilla-Vs-Kong-Has-Wrapped-In-Australia-According-To-The-Director}}</ref> That same month, Wingard revealed [[Hong Kong]] as one of the final shooting locations and that principal photography had wrapped.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ew.com/movies/2019/04/20/godzilla-vs-kong/ |title=Godzilla vs. Kong wraps shooting |first=Clark |last=Collis |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=April 20, 2019 |accessdate=April 20, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=April 20, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420223019/https://ew.com/movies/2019/04/20/godzilla-vs-kong/}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n===Marketing===\nIn May 2019, the first promotional one-sheet poster was revealed at the Licensing Expo.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://collider.com/godzilla-vs-kong-dune-promo-posters/ |title=New Promo Posters for \u2018Godzilla vs Kong\u2019 and \u2018Dune\u2019 Tease the Titanic 2020 Titles |first=Dave |last=Trumbore |work=Collider |date=May 30, 2019 |accessdate=May 31, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=May 31, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531091732/http://collider.com/godzilla-vs-kong-dune-promo-posters/}}</ref> In June 2019, Warner Bros screened an early look to European exhibitors at CineEurope.<ref name=\"CineEurope\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-bros-godzilla-vs-kong-it2-joker-wonder-woman-lionsgate-rian-johnson-knives-out-studiocanal-cineeurope-1202633778/ |title=Warner Bros Teases Horror, DC, \u2018Godzilla Vs Kong\u2019; Studiocanal Goes \u2018Radioactive\u2019 \u2013 CineEurope |first=Nancy |last=Tartaglione |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=June 17, 2019 |accessdate=June 17, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=June 17, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190618043628/https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-bros-godzilla-vs-kong-it2-joker-wonder-woman-lionsgate-rian-johnson-knives-out-studiocanal-cineeurope-1202633778/}}</ref> In August 2019, it was announced that Disruptor Beam will develop a mobile game to tie-in for the film's release.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://cosmicbook.news/godzilla-vs-kong-poster-game |title=Godzilla vs. Kong Poster teases one will fall;Game in Development |first=Matt |last=McGloin |work=Cosmic Book News |date=August 10, 2019 |accessdate=August 11, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=August 11, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811215337/https://cosmicbook.news/godzilla-vs-kong-poster-game}}</ref> In December 2019, a brief clip was revealed during a Warner Bros. reel at [[Comic Con Experience]], and later leaked online.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2486314/whoa-kong-punches-godzilla-in-super-brief-but-badass-godzilla-vs-kong-footage|title=Whoa, Kong Punches Godzilla In Super-Brief But Badass Godzilla Vs. Kong Footage|author=Gina Carbone|work=CinemaBlend|date=December 8, 2019|accessdate=December 8, 2019|url-status=live|archivedate=December 8, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209011305/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2486314/whoa-kong-punches-godzilla-in-super-brief-but-badass-godzilla-vs-kong-footage}}</ref> In January 2020, images from the Hong Kong Toys & Games Fair displaying figures (including a [[Mechagodzilla]] figure) related to the film were leaked online, sparking speculation whether the film would include Mechagodzilla.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2487983/godzilla-vs-kong-might-be-bringing-in-an-iconic-kaiju|title=Godzilla Vs. Kong Might Be Bringing In An Iconic Kaiju|author=Adam Holmes|work=Cinema Blend|date=January 7, 2020|accessdate=January 7, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=January 7, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200108042635/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2487983/godzilla-vs-kong-might-be-bringing-in-an-iconic-kaiju}}</ref> In February 2020, Toho and Legendary announced the ''Godzilla vs. Kong'' Publishing Program and licensees. Through the publishing program, Legendary plans to release two graphic novels, an art book, novelizations, and children\u2019s books. Amongst the licensees named were [[Playmates Toys]], Bioworld, Rubies, Funko, 60Out, and the Virtual Reality Company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2020/02/20/toho-and-legendary-announce-licensees-for-godzilla-vs-kong/|title=Toho and Legendary Announce Licensees for Godzilla vs. Kong|author1=Chris Mowry|author2=Jacara Jenkins|work=SciFi Japan|date=February 20, 2020|accessdate=February 20, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=February 20, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221062043/http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2020/02/20/toho-and-legendary-announce-licensees-for-godzilla-vs-kong/}}</ref>\n\n===Theatrical===\n''Godzilla vs. Kong'' is scheduled to be released in the United States on November 20, 2020, in 2D, [[3D film|3D]], and [[IMAX]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/godzilla-kong-release-date-pushed-8-months-november-2020-1253500|title='Godzilla vs. Kong' Release Date Pushed 8 Months to November 2020|author=Aaron Couch|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=November 25, 2019|accessdate=November 25, 2019|url-status=live|archivedate=November 25, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191126074636/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/godzilla-kong-release-date-pushed-8-months-november-2020-1253500}}</ref> It will be distributed by [[Warner Bros.|Warner Bros. Pictures]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/space-jam-2-release-date-godzilla-vs-kong-annabelle-sequel-warner-bros-1202562428/ |title=Warner Bros Dates \u2018Space Jam 2\u2019, Shifts \u2018Annabelle\u2019 Sequel & \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 |first=Erik |last=Pedersen |work=Deadline |date=February 21, 2019 |accessdate=February 21, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=February 21, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222025700/https://deadline.com/2019/02/space-jam-2-release-date-godzilla-vs-kong-annabelle-sequel-warner-bros-1202562428/}}</ref> except in Japan where it will be distributed by [[Toho]].<ref name=\"Press Release\"/> The film was previously scheduled to be released on May 29, May 22, and March 13, 2020.<ref name=\"May10\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/warner-bros-moves-dates-godzilla-892634 |title=Warner Bros. Moves Dates For 'Godzilla 2,' 'Godzilla vs Kong' |last=Rahman |first=Abid |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=May 10, 2016 |accessdate=May 10, 2016|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6pLyTqstH?url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/warner-bros-moves-dates-godzilla-892634#|archive-date=March 30, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-studio-toby-emmerich-peter-roth-dc-netflix-godzilla-vs-kong-kevin-tsujihara-1202629538/ |title=Warner Bros. Bosses Toby Emmerich & Peter Roth On Studio Post Kevin Tsujihara In Streaming Era, Disney/Fox & Potential \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 Move \u2013 Produced By |first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=June 8, 2019 |accessdate=June 9, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=June 9, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609070404/https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-studio-toby-emmerich-peter-roth-dc-netflix-godzilla-vs-kong-kevin-tsujihara-1202629538/}}</ref><ref name=\"new date\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/space-jam-2-release-date-godzilla-vs-kong-annabelle-sequel-warner-bros-1202562428/ |title=Warner Bros Dates \u2018Space Jam 2\u2019, Shifts \u2018Annabelle\u2019 Sequel & \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 |last=Pedersen |first=Erik |work=Deadline |date=February 21, 2019 |accessdate=February 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222025700/https://deadline.com/2019/02/space-jam-2-release-date-godzilla-vs-kong-annabelle-sequel-warner-bros-1202562428/|archive-date=February 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In February 2020, Warner Bros. hosted an unannounced test screening, which received a positive response.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2491108/check-out-godzilla-vs-kongs-directors-cryptic-post-following-reported-test-screening|title=Check Out Godzilla Vs. Kong's Director\u2019s Cryptic Post Following Reported Test Screening|author=Adam Holmes|work=Cinema Blend|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=March 11, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=March 11, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312012236/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2491108/check-out-godzilla-vs-kongs-directors-cryptic-post-following-reported-test-screening}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n=== Citations ===\n{{Reflist|refs=}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n* {{cite book |last=Kalat |first=David |year=2010 |title=A Critical History and Filmography of Toho's Godzilla Series - Second Edition |publisher=McFarland |isbn=9780786447497 |ref=harv}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|5034838|Godzilla vs. Kong}}\n{{MonsterVerse}}\n{{Godzilla}}\n{{KingKong}}\n{{Adam Wingard}}\n\n[[Category:Upcoming films]]\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n[[Category:2020 3D films]]\n[[Category:2020s monster movies]]\n[[Category:2020s sequel films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American 3D films]]\n[[Category:Crossover films]]\n[[Category:Films set in the Atlantic Ocean]]\n[[Category:Films set in Berlin]]\n[[Category:Films set in Brisbane]]\n[[Category:Films set in Hawaii]]\n[[Category:Films set in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Films s